### =============================================
### USER API REQUESTS with Auto-Capture
### =============================================

### 1. Create User (auto-captures userId for subsequent requests)
POST http://localhost:8080/users/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "gvgvgvkjsjndfn",
  "email": "john@exampjsfd5le.com",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("userId", response.body.id);
    client.global.set("username", response.body.username);
%}

### 2. Create Second User
POST http://localhost:8080/users/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "janesmith",
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "password": "password456"
}

### 3. Get User By ID (uses captured userId from request #1)
GET http://localhost:8080/users/{{userId}}

### 4. Get User By Username
GET http://localhost:8080/users/username/{{username}}

### 5. Get User By Email
GET http://localhost:8080/users/email/john@example.com

### 6. Get All Users
GET http://localhost:8080/users/

### 7. Get All Active Users
GET http://localhost:8080/users/active

### 8. Check If Username Exists
GET http://localhost:8080/users/exists/username/johndoe

### 9. Check If Email Exists
GET http://localhost:8080/users/exists/email/john@example.com

### 10. Update User
PUT http://localhost:8080/users/{{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jonathan",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "jonathan@example.com",
  "password": "newpassword123",
  "isActive": true
}

### 11. Soft Delete User (sets isActive = false)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/users/{{userId}}

### 12. Hard Delete User (removes from database)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/users/{{userId}}/hard